Third-party software
--------------------

Reawa is a native Swift application. It does not bundle third-party open-source
libraries. At runtime it uses macOS system frameworks (AppKit, SwiftUI,
Security, CoreHID, and others) and invokes system tools provided by the
operating system:

  - OpenSSH (`/usr/bin/ssh`, `/usr/bin/ssh-keygen`) — OpenSSH License
  - `ifconfig` — part of macOS user-space tools

When distributing a built application (e.g. Reawa.app), include this NOTICE file
in the app bundle or release archive.

